energy = pulse_widths * (intensity / intensity_mean)  # Using univariate correlation with power and energy as an example

intensities = target_thicknesses * intensity / 10
pows = pulse_widths * (energy / energy_mean + 0.8) # Using bivariate correlation with power and energy as an example
